From 88a1b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: System233 <cdkeylzh@outlook.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Include global extralibs in extralibs_avutil

On Windows, libavutil uses Crypt* functions (CryptAcquireContextA,
CryptReleaseContext, CryptGenRandom) from advapi32.dll. The configure
script detects this via check_lib wincrypt and adds -ladvapi32 to the
global $extralibs variable. However, extralibs_avutil was set to
"$LIBRT $LIBDRM $LIBM" without $extralibs, unlike avcodec/avformat/
avdevice/avfilter which use "$extralibs". This caused libavutil.pc to
omit -ladvapi32, leading to unresolved external symbol errors when
downstream projects link against avutil without the transitive
dependency chain providing advapi32.

Fix by appending $extralibs to extralibs_avutil.
---
 configure | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index c2ddab0..360c066 100644
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -7128,7 +7128,7 @@ source_path=${source_path}
 LIBPREF=${LIBPREF}
 LIBSUF=${LIBSUF}
 
-extralibs_avutil="$LIBRT $LIBDRM $LIBM"
+extralibs_avutil="$LIBRT $LIBDRM $LIBM $extralibs"
 extralibs_avcodec="$extralibs"
 extralibs_avformat="$extralibs"
 extralibs_avdevice="$extralibs"
-- 
